    @wraps(f)
    def decorated_function(*args, **kwargs):
        # Check basic auth for all users
        is_auth, user_id = check_basic_auth()
        
        # For paid users accessing sensitive features, require enhanced auth
        if is_paid_user(user_id) and is_sensitive_route():
            enhanced_auth = check_photo_auth(user_id)
            if not enhanced_auth:
                return redirect(url_for('auth.photo_challenge'))
        
        return f(*args, **kwargs)
    return decorated_function
Conversion Psychology
Current Problem: Photo auth creates doubt ("Is this legit? Why do they need my photo?") Solution: Remove friction for evaluation, add security as premium value

Free Tier Message: "Try it risk-free" Upgrade Message: "Protect your valuable conversations with enhanced security"

This approach lets users experience the value first, then choose enhanced security when they're ready to pay. Much better conversion funnel!

